Key Match Events: Bhuvneshwar gets his second. Scott Edwards miscues a slower ball, and Netherlands are 89 for 7.

R Ashwin has bowled a mesmerising spell so far, getting the ball to drift and swing both ways. Now he's bagged his first two wickets of the World Cup, Colin Ackermann and Tom Cooper caught on the leg-side boundary in the space of four balls. Netherlands are 63 for 5 in 12.4 overs.
Max O'Dowd is bowled by Axar Patel
Virat Kohli took a running catch to dismiss Tim Pringle
Suryakumar Yadav won the Player-of-the-Match award for his 51* off 25 balls
Post-Match Reflections: Suryakumar Yadav, the Player of the Match, said, "I was just trying to express myself when I went in to bat. Message was clear when I went in. We needed to get 8-10 runs an over to ensure we had a total for our bowlers to defend."
